  "response_text": "I can tell that you're feeling really overwhelmed and uncertain about your abilities right now. It's like you're wondering if you're truly cut out for this, if you're good enough, or if you're just pretending to be someone you're not. \n\nFirst of all, let me tell you that you're not alone in feeling this way. Many people, even those who seem incredibly confident and successful, struggle with imposter syndrome. It's a common phenomenon where you doubt your abilities and feel like you're just faking it.\n\nBut here's the thing: you're not faking it. You're actually doing your best, and that's something to be proud of. It takes a lot of courage to put yourself out there and try new things, even when you're not entirely sure you'll succeed.\n\nIt's also worth remembering that everyone has strengths and weaknesses. Nobody is perfect, and nobody has all the answers. Even the people who seem like they do are often just as uncertain",
